        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 2:21PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 221 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Northstar, or near Prosser Creek Reservoir, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Prosser Creek Reservoir, Glenshire-Devonshire Cdp, Hirschdale,
Truckee, Granite Flat Campground, Lakeside Campground,
Glenshire-Devonshire, Ca 89 At Placer-Nevada Co Line, Alpine Meadows
Campground, Hobart Mills, Boca Campground, Truckee-Tahoe Airport, and
Donner Memorial Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
